Instead of hardcoding the provider.tf file we can leave it empty
We can create a file with extension hcl and provide the backend configuration
You can intilzed the same with terraform init backend-config=nameofthehcl file. 

Using the same terraform code we can create dev test staging prod environment. We need to seprate the backend setting from your terraform configuration we will make easy to use in different backend for dev test staging prod
#go to the provider block in the backend block remove all the content
 backend "s3" {}
####lets create a new file backend-dev.hcl
bucket = "gopal-tfstate-good-hen" #change the bucketname as per your bucket name
key = "dev/project-hail-marry.tfstate"
region = "us-east-1"
